<topic id="opening-existing-documents">
  <title>Opening Documents</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Opening file</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To open a document in <ph keyref="product"/>, do one of the following:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Go to <menucascade product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
          <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Open File</uicontrol>
        </menucascade><ph product="author developer editor"><menucascade>
            <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol><image href="../img/Open16.png" id="image_dhj_23p_sr"/>Open (<shortcut
                conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_o_shortcut"/>)</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> or click the <uicontrol><image href="../img/Open16.png"
              id="image_myk_rjp_sr"/>Open</uicontrol> toolbar button</ph> to display the
          <uicontrol>Open File</uicontrol> dialog box.<ph product="author developer editor"> The
          start folder of this dialog box can be either the last folder visited by this dialog box
          or the folder of the currently selected file. This can be <xref keyref="options_global"
            >configured in the Global preferences page.</xref></ph></li>
      <li>Go to <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Open URL</uicontrol>
        </menucascade><ph product="author developer editor"> or click the <uicontrol><image
              href="../img/OpenURL16.png" id="image_gn2_y3p_sr"/>Open URL</uicontrol> toolbar
          button</ph> to display a dialog box where you can specify a URL (defined by a protocol,
        host, resource path, and an optional port) or use the browsing actions in the
            <uicontrol><image href="../img/URL_Drop.png" id="image_n4x_qrn_ps"/>Browse for remote
          file</uicontrol> drop-down menu.</li>
      <li product="author developer editor">Click the <uicontrol><image
            href="../img/OpenResource16.png" id="image_k5h_gkp_sr"/>Open/Find Resource</uicontrol>
        toolbar button to search for a file to open. </li>
      <li product="author developer editor">Go to <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol><image href="../img/Refresh16.png" id="image_dx5_bfw_sr"/>Reload</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> to load the last saved file content. All unsaved modifications are lost. </li>
      <li product="author developer editor">Go to <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Reopen</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> to reopen one of the recently opened document files. The list containing
        recently opened files can be emptied by invoking the <uicontrol>Clear history</uicontrol>
        action.</li>
      <li>Select the <uicontrol>Open</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>Open with</uicontrol> action from the
        contextual menu of the <xref href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"
            ><uicontrol product="author developer editor">Project</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Navigator</uicontrol>
        view</xref>.</li>
    </ul>
  </body>
